00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:19.000
Succès cake layers

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:26.000
To make succès cake layers, 

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:40.000
you will need 250g of egg whites, 250g of caster sugar, 250g of ground almonds and 50g of flour.

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:52.000
First whip the egg whites using a mixer and add a little bit of sugar to help them get stiff.

00:01:45.000 --> 00:01:51.000
Incorporate the flour, ground almonds and sugar.

00:02:13.000 --> 00:02:18.000
The mix is ready to use once homogeneous.

00:02:22.000 --> 00:02:26.000
Make succès layers using a piping bag.

00:02:56.000 --> 00:03:03.000
Bake in a preheated oven at 180°C for about 12 min.

00:03:15.000 --> 00:03:23.000
The succès layers are ready to use to make entremets. Done!

